51.2	Peppermint	Peppermint	Peppermint is a hybrid mint, a cross between watermint and spearmint. The plant, indigenous to Europe, is now widespread in cultivation throughout all regions of the world. It is found wild occasionally with its parent species.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/72/Pfefferminze_natur_peppermint.jpg/220px-Pfefferminze_natur_peppermint.jpg
